# v3 Simplified UI Context

## Design principles

- **State-driven background**: Fatigue state (fresh/optimal/trained/fatigued/overtrained) drives full-page gradient (weather-app style). Use `STATE_GRADIENTS[fatigueState]` on root wrapper.
- **Slim header**: One row — [Sporty Gotchi] [Lv N] [Friends] [Locker] [Settings]. No Edit Profile/Disconnect/Achievements in bar; those live in SettingsPanel.
- **Hero-first**: Main view = avatar + one-line status only. Use `getShortStateDescription(fatigueState)` under the avatar. Single column `max-w-lg mx-auto`.
- **Progressive disclosure**: Recovery, Challenges, Training details, Recent activities, Streaks are collapsible sections below the Locker; all collapsed by default.
- **Single column**: No 4-column grid; no gamification sidebar on main view. One focal area (avatar as hero).

## Key files

| Purpose | File(s) |
|---------|---------|
| Page layout, header, hero, sections | `app/page.tsx` |
| State → gradient map | `app/page.tsx` or `lib/ui/state-theme.ts` |
| Short status copy | `lib/training-metrics.ts` (`getShortStateDescription`) |
| Settings drawer | `components/SettingsPanel.tsx` |
| Collapsible wrapper | `components/CollapsibleSection.tsx` |
| Metric cards (in Training details section) | `components/MetricCard.tsx` |

## Conventions

- Locker section has `id="locker"` for header scroll target.
- Header Locker button: `document.getElementById('locker')?.scrollIntoView({ block: 'start' })`.
- Use existing `SetupScreen`, `AchievementGrid`, `RecoveryMeter`, `RestDayLogger`, `ChallengeCard`, `StreakDisplay`, `TrainingGraph` inside collapsible sections; do not remove them.
- Extract `MetricCard` from page into `components/MetricCard.tsx`; keep same props (label, value, icon, color).
